            "folder": "zDlxATrLAlbYA2Mv",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/spells/scrying.webp",
            "name": "Scrying",
            "sort": 200000,
            "system": {
                "area": null,
                "cost": {
                    "value": ""
                },
                "counteraction": false,
                "damage": {},
                "defense": {
                    "save": {
                        "basic": false,
                        "statistic": "will"
                    }
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>You magically spy on a creature of your choice. <em>Scrying</em> works like @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Clairvoyance], except that the image you receive is less precise, insufficient for <em>teleport</em> and similar spells. Instead of creating an eye in a set location within 500 feet, you instead create an eye that manifests just above the target. You can choose a target either by name or by touching one of its possessions or a piece of its body. If you haven't met the target in person, <em>scrying</em>'s DC is 2 lower, and if you are unaware of the target's identity (perhaps because you found an unknown creature's fang at a crime scene), the DC is instead 10 lower.</p>\n<p>The effect of <em>scrying</em> depends on the target's Will save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The spell fails and the target is temporarily immune for 1 week. The target also gains a glimpse of you and learns its rough distance and direction from you.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The spell fails and the target is temporarily immune for 1 day.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The spell succeeds.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The spell succeeds, and the eye follows the target if it moves, traveling up to 60 feet per round.</p>"
                },
                "duration": {
                    "sustained": true,
                    "value": "10 minutes"
                },
                "level": {
                    "value": 6
                },
                "location": {
