            "system": {
                "baseItem": null,
                "bulk": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "containerId": null,
                "description": {
                    "gm": "<p>Each Arudora memento is unique in appearance, but all seven are approximately the same size. Carried by each of the cursed family members, these mementos have within them the power to unlock entire portions of Bastardhall from the ghostly cursed state the castle traditionally exists in.</p><hr><p><strong>Activate—Return Memento</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">3</span> (manipulate) You place the memento into the appropriate statue's clutches in the fountain located in area <strong>B3</strong> of Bastardhall. The statue briefly animates to claim the memento, which turns to stone and becomes thereafter a permanent part of the statue, effectively destroying the memento while granting a boon to the party that persists for the remainder of this Adventure Path. When this elegant crimson hand fan is Returned, the dungeon (detailed in Chapter 5) is unlocked. The souls trapped in Bastardhall appreciate the end of Alisendra's dominion and now whisper hints of truths in the ears of those who seek knowledge. The DCs for all checks made to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Recall Knowledge] are reduced by 1 for the rest of the Adventure Path.</p><hr><p><strong>Destruction</strong> An Arudora memento is destroyed when it's activated with Return Memento, and the boon it grants upon this returning lasts until the very end of the Adventure Path.</p>",
                    "value": ""
