            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-monster-core-2.Actor.Jbc4BC6wv9GLtoY7.Item.Gml3vx4hRf5j1StT"
            },
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Borrowed Skin",
            "sort": 1200000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Alisandra's \"borrowed skin\" is her own skin from her previous life.</p><hr /><p>A blood hag wears a covering of skin stolen from a humanoid creature they've killed, hiding their true form. They appear as the creature whose skin they're wearing, including to spells that would detect that creature. Creatures can still potentially detect the deception as described in the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Impersonate] action.</p>\n<p>Spreading coarse salt inside the skin prevents the hag from putting it back on, forcing them to keep their fiery form until they kill another humanoid and spend 1 hour turning it into a new disguise.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "NdNOpjTKmmNAo6Oi",
